verbs.description: divebomb (third-person singular simple present divebombs, present participle divebombing, simple past and past participle divebombed)

entries.meaning: (of an aircraft) To bomb whilst in a steep dive.
(of a bird) To attack (especially the head of) a person or animal that strays into their territory.
(auto racing) To attempt an overtake by braking very late on corner entry (involving contact).
(of a motorist) To overtake slower traffic by way of a more circuitous route, such as a pair of freeway exit and entrance ramps.
